content:
GitHub shows 59 PRs are currently waiting on bors: https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pulls?q=is%3Apr+is%3Aopen+label%3AS-waiting-on-bors+

But rustc-pr-tracking shows 33: https://rust-lang.github.io/rustc-pr-tracking/

It seems unlikely to me that 30 PRs were approved since the page was last generated, so I'd assume there's a bug in rustc-pr-tracking.

pr-trackings total counts are all a bit strange..
https://github.com/rust-lang/rustc-pr-tracking/issues/10
It looks like there were ~30 prs approved in the past 24 hours. dtolnay approved at least 10, and some other people approved a bunch as well.
So maybe it's not a bug after all.
@Eric Huss Out of curiosity, how did you estimate that number?

I just vaguely remember the state of the queue yesterday when I closed the tree, and then looked at the opened PR list.

Can also run a query like https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pulls?q=is%3Apr+is%3Aopen+label%3AS-waiting-on-bors+The+tree+is+currently+closed to see which ones were added since then.
Looks like the pr-tracker just updated and it has 59 waiting.
I guess reviewers were just really productive recently :)
Also in some part due to the GHA outage earlier today
There are PRs in the queue that have been approved for 2 days
Yeah our CI was blocked for roughly a day
Ah, that would explain why the queue got so long

https://rust-lang.zulipchat.com/#narrow/stream/242791-t-infra/topic/aarch64.20job.20runner.20delayed

only waiting for ~2-3 days of rollup=never PRs now :upside_down:
